95// loadSchemeDataToDialog =====================================================
97//=============================================================================
98static void loadSchemeDataToDialog( HWND hWndDialog )
99{
100
101 // load the name of the current scheme
102 SetDlgItemText( hWndDialog, STATIC_CURRENT_SCHEME,
103 theScheme->getSchemeFilename() );
104
105 // load the state combo box with every option available
106 SendDlgItemMessage( hWndDialog, COMBO_STATE, CB_RESETCONTENT, 0, 0 );
107 LoadStateCombo( GWS_PUSH_BUTTON |
108 GWS_RADIO_BUTTON |
109 GWS_CHECK_BOX |
110 GWS_PROGRESS_BAR |
111 GWS_SCROLL_LISTBOX |
112 GWS_HORZ_SLIDER |
113 GWS_VERT_SLIDER |
114 GWS_STATIC_TEXT |
115 GWS_ENTRY_FIELD |
116 GWS_USER_WINDOW |
117 GWS_COMBO_BOX,
118 GetDlgItem( hWndDialog, COMBO_STATE ) );
119
120 // load the image combo box with the images from the gui collection
121 SendDlgItemMessage( hWndDialog, COMBO_IMAGE, CB_RESETCONTENT, 0, 0 );
122 LoadImageListComboBox( GetDlgItem( hWndDialog, COMBO_IMAGE ) );
123
124 //
125 // load our own internal table of images and colors to the
126 // property dialog tables
127 //
128 Int i;
129 ImageAndColorInfo *info;
130 for( i = FIRST_VALID_IDENTIFIER; i < NUM_STATE_IDENTIFIERS; i++ )
131 {
132
133 info = theScheme->getImageAndColor( (StateIdentifier)i );
134 assert( info );
135 StoreImageAndColor( info->stateID,
136 info->image,
137 info->color,
138 info->borderColor );
139
140 } // end for i
141
142 // switch to the generic state
143 SwitchToState( GENERIC_ENABLED, hWndDialog );
144
145 // load the text color combo
146 SendDlgItemMessage( hWndDialog, COMBO_TEXT_STATE, CB_RESETCONTENT, 0, 0 );
147 LoadTextStateCombo( GetDlgItem( hWndDialog, COMBO_TEXT_STATE ),
148 theScheme->getEnabledTextColor(),
149 theScheme->getEnabledTextBorderColor(),
150 theScheme->getDisabledTextColor(),
151 theScheme->getDisabledTextBorderColor(),
152 theScheme->getHiliteTextColor(),
153 theScheme->getHiliteTextBorderColor() );
154
155 // load the font combo if present
156 SendDlgItemMessage( hWndDialog, COMBO_FONT, CB_RESETCONTENT, 0, 0 );
157 LoadFontCombo( GetDlgItem( hWndDialog, COMBO_FONT ), theScheme->getFont() );
158
159} // end loadSchemeDataToDialog
160
161// saveData ===================================================================
162//=============================================================================
163static void saveData( HWND hWndDialog )
164{
165
166 //
167 // copy the image and color data from the property tables to our
168 // own
169 //
170 Int i;
171 ImageAndColorInfo *info;
172 for( i = FIRST_VALID_IDENTIFIER; i < NUM_STATE_IDENTIFIERS; i++ )
173 {
174
175 info = GetStateInfo( (StateIdentifier)i );
176 assert( info );
177 theScheme->storeImageAndColor( info->stateID,
178 info->image,
179 info->color,
180 info->borderColor );
181
182 } // end for i
183
184 // save default text colors
185 theScheme->setEnabledTextColor( GetPropsEnabledTextColor() );
186 theScheme->setEnabledTextBorderColor( GetPropsEnabledTextBorderColor() );
187 theScheme->setDisabledTextColor( GetPropsDisabledTextColor() );
188 theScheme->setDisabledTextBorderColor( GetPropsDisabledTextBorderColor() );
189 theScheme->setHiliteTextColor( GetPropsHiliteTextColor() );
190 theScheme->setHiliteTextBorderColor( GetPropsHiliteTextBorderColor() );
191
192 // save the font
193 theScheme->setFont( GetSelectedFontFromCombo( GetDlgItem( hWndDialog, COMBO_FONT ) ) );
194
195} // end saveData

197// saveAsDialog ===============================================================
200//=============================================================================
201char *saveAsDialog( void )
202{
203 static char filename[ _MAX_PATH ];
204 OPENFILENAME ofn;
205 Bool returnCode;
206 char filter[] = "Layout Scheme Files (*.ls)\0*.ls\0" \
207 "All Files (*.*)\0*.*\0\0" ;
208
209 ofn.lStructSize = sizeof( OPENFILENAME );
210 ofn.hwndOwner = TheEditor->getWindowHandle();
211 ofn.hInstance = NULL;
212 ofn.lpstrFilter = filter;
213 ofn.lpstrCustomFilter = NULL;
214 ofn.nMaxCustFilter = 0;
215 ofn.nFilterIndex = 0;
216 ofn.lpstrFile = filename;
217 ofn.nMaxFile = _MAX_PATH;
218 ofn.lpstrFileTitle = NULL;
219 ofn.nMaxFileTitle = 0;
220 ofn.lpstrInitialDir = NULL;
221 ofn.lpstrTitle = NULL;
222 ofn.Flags = OFN_NOREADONLYRETURN | OFN_OVERWRITEPROMPT | OFN_PATHMUSTEXIST | OFN_NOCHANGEDIR;
223 ofn.nFileOffset = 0;
224 ofn.nFileExtension = 0;
225 ofn.lpstrDefExt = "ls";
226 ofn.lCustData = 0L ;
227 ofn.lpfnHook = NULL ;
228 ofn.lpTemplateName = NULL ;
229
230 returnCode = GetSaveFileName( &ofn );
231
232 if( returnCode )
233 return filename;
234 else
235 return NULL;
236
237} // end saveAsDialog

281// layoutSchemeCallback =======================================================
283//=============================================================================
284static LRESULT CALLBACK layoutSchemeCallback( HWND hWndDialog,
285 UINT message,
286 WPARAM wParam,
287 LPARAM lParam )
288{
289 Int returnCode;
290
291 //
292 // this is largely based on the property dialog code so lets just
293 // let the default handle code work here too
294 //
295 if( HandleCommonDialogMessages( hWndDialog, message,
296 wParam, lParam, &returnCode ) == TRUE )
297 return returnCode;
298
299 switch( message )
300 {
301
302 // ------------------------------------------------------------------------
303 case WM_INITDIALOG:
304 {
305
306 // load the dialog engine and items with the current data of the scheme
307 loadSchemeDataToDialog( hWndDialog );
308 break;
309
310 } // end init dialog
311
312 // ------------------------------------------------------------------------
313 case WM_COMMAND:
314 {
315// Int notifyCode = HIWORD( wParam ); // notification code
316 Int controlID = LOWORD( wParam ); // control ID
317// HWND hWndControl = (HWND)lParam; // control window handle
318
319 switch( controlID )
320 {
321
322 // --------------------------------------------------------------------
323 case BUTTON_APPLY_SCHEME:
324 {
325 Int result;
326
327 //
328 // this will take the scheme settings currently loaded as the
329 // "working scheme" to ALL windows and gadgets in the current
330 // layout, because this is such a large sweeping change we will
331 // ask them if they are sure
332 //
333 result = MessageBox( NULL, "This will apply these scheme color and image settings to ALL windows and gadgets currently loaded in the edit window. Are you sure you want to proceed?",
334 "Are You Sure?", MB_YESNO | MB_ICONWARNING );
335 if( result == IDNO )
336 break;
337
338 //
339 // change all the windows to have the settings loaded in the
340 // current working scheme in the state identifier entry tables,
341 // note that we are applying the scheme in the property
342 // entry tables and NOT the scheme in "theScheme", this is to
343 // allow people to load a scheme file, or edit the parameters
344 // and apply those changes to controls without changing the
345 // current layout scheme.
346 //
347 theScheme->applyPropertyTablesToWindow( TheWindowManager->winGetWindowList() );
348
349 //
350 // also apply these changes to the window lists in the clipboard
351 // just to be complete
352 //
353 theScheme->applyPropertyTablesToWindow( TheGUIEditWindowManager->getClipboardList() );
354 theScheme->applyPropertyTablesToWindow( TheGUIEditWindowManager->getClipboardDupeList() );
355
356 break;
357
358 } // end apply scheme
359
360 // --------------------------------------------------------------------
361 case BUTTON_SAVE:
362 {
363 char *filename = saveAsDialog();
364
365 if( theScheme && filename )
366 {
367
368 saveData( hWndDialog );
369 theScheme->saveScheme( filename );
370 SetDlgItemText( hWndDialog, STATIC_CURRENT_SCHEME,
371 theScheme->getSchemeFilename() );
372
373 } // end if
374
375 break;
376
377 } // end save
378
379 // --------------------------------------------------------------------
380 case BUTTON_LOAD:
381 {
382 char *filename = openDialog();
383
384 if( theScheme && filename )
385 {
386
387 // load the new data
388 if( theScheme->loadScheme( filename ) )
389 {
390
391 // load the dialog engine and items with the current data of the scheme
392 loadSchemeDataToDialog( hWndDialog );
393
394 } // end if
395 else
396 {
397
398 MessageBox( TheEditor->getWindowHandle(),
399 "Unable to open scheme file.", "Error", MB_OK );
400
401 } // end else
402
403 } // end if
404
405 break;
406
407 } // end load
408
409 // --------------------------------------------------------------------
410 case IDOK:
411
412 saveData( hWndDialog );
413 theScheme->saveScheme( theScheme->getSchemeFilename() );
414 EndDialog( hWndDialog, TRUE );
415 break;
416
417 // --------------------------------------------------------------------
418 case IDCANCEL:
419
420 // do nothing, just get outta here!
421 EndDialog( hWndDialog, FALSE );
422 break;
423
424 } // end switch
425
426 break;
427
428 } // end command
429
430 } // end switch, message
431
432 return 0;
433
434} // end layoutSchemeCallback

1496// LayoutScheme::~LayoutScheme ================================================
1498//=============================================================================
1499LayoutScheme::~LayoutScheme( void )
1500{
1501 Int i;
1502
1503 // free all the state name strings
1504 for( i = 0; i < NUM_STATE_IDENTIFIERS; i++ )
1505 {
1506
1507 if( m_imageAndColorTable[ i ].stateName )
1508 {
1509

1511 m_imageAndColorTable[ i ].stateName = NULL;
1512
1513 } // end if
1514
1515 } // end for i
1516
1517} // end ~LayoutScheme
1518
1519// LayoutScheme::init =========================================================
1521//=============================================================================
1522void LayoutScheme::init( void )
1523{
1524 Int i;
1525 ImageAndColorInfo *info;
1526
1527 // just up the default state values
1528 for( i = FIRST_VALID_IDENTIFIER; i < NUM_STATE_IDENTIFIERS; i++ )
1529 {
1530
1531 // get info from the static table created for property editing
1532 info = GetStateInfo( (StateIdentifier)i );
1533 assert( info );
1534 m_imageAndColorTable[ i ].windowType = info->windowType;
1535 m_imageAndColorTable[ i ].stateID = info->stateID;
1536 m_imageAndColorTable[ i ].image = info->image;
1537 m_imageAndColorTable[ i ].color = info->color;
1538 m_imageAndColorTable[ i ].borderColor = info->borderColor;
1539 m_imageAndColorTable[ i ].stateName = new char[strlen( info->stateName ) + 1];
1540 strcpy(m_imageAndColorTable[ i ].stateName, info->stateName );
1541
1542 } // end for i
1543
1544 // assign a default set of colors
1545 UnsignedByte alpha = 255;
1546 Color red = GameMakeColor( 255, 0, 0, alpha );
1547 Color darkRed = GameMakeColor( 128, 0, 0, alpha );
1548 Color lightRed = GameMakeColor( 255, 128, 128, alpha );
1549 Color green = GameMakeColor( 0, 255, 0, alpha );
1550 Color darkGreen = GameMakeColor( 0, 128, 0, alpha );
1551 Color lightGreen = GameMakeColor( 128, 255, 128, alpha );
1552 Color blue = GameMakeColor( 0, 0, 255, alpha );
1553 Color darkBlue = GameMakeColor( 0, 0, 128, alpha );
1554 Color lightBlue = GameMakeColor( 128, 128, 255, alpha );
1555// Color purple = GameMakeColor( 255, 0, 255, alpha );
1556// Color darkPurple = GameMakeColor( 128, 0, 128, alpha );
1557// Color lightPurple = GameMakeColor( 255, 128, 255, alpha );
1558 Color yellow = GameMakeColor( 255, 255, 0, alpha );
1559// Color darkYellow = GameMakeColor( 128, 128, 0, alpha );
1560// Color lightYellow = GameMakeColor( 255, 255, 128, alpha );
1561// Color cyan = GameMakeColor( 0, 255, 255, alpha );
1562// Color darkCyan = GameMakeColor( 64, 128, 128, alpha );
1563// Color lightCyan = GameMakeColor( 128, 255, 255, alpha );
1564 Color gray = GameMakeColor( 128, 128, 128, alpha );
1565 Color darkGray = GameMakeColor( 64, 64, 64, alpha );
1566 Color lightGray = GameMakeColor( 192, 192, 192, alpha );
1567 Color black = GameMakeColor( 0, 0, 0, alpha );
1568 Color white = GameMakeColor( 254, 254, 254, alpha );
1569 const Image *image;
1570
1571 // push button
1572 image = TheMappedImageCollection->findImageByName( AsciiString( "PushButtonEnabled" ) );
1573 storeImageAndColor( BUTTON_ENABLED, image, red, lightRed );
1574 image = TheMappedImageCollection->findImageByName( AsciiString( "PushButtonEnabledSelected" ) );
1575 storeImageAndColor( BUTTON_ENABLED_PUSHED, image, yellow, white );
1576 image = TheMappedImageCollection->findImageByName( AsciiString( "PushButtonDisabled" ) );
1577 storeImageAndColor( BUTTON_DISABLED, image, gray, lightGray );

2331// LayoutScheme::loadScheme ===================================================
2333//=============================================================================
2334Bool LayoutScheme::loadScheme( char *filename )
2335{
2336 FILE *fp;
2337 UnsignedByte colorR, colorG, colorB, colorA,
2338 bColorR, bColorG, bColorB, bColorA;
2339
2340 // open the file
2341 fp = fopen( filename, "r" );
2342 if( fp == NULL )
2343 return FALSE;
2344
2345 // save the filename we're using now
2346 setSchemeFilename( filename );
2347
2348 // write header
2349 Int version;
2350 fscanf( fp, "Window Layout Scheme: Version '%d'\n", &version );
2351 if( version != SCHEME_VERSION )
2352 {
2353
2354 DEBUG_LOG(( "loadScheme: Old layout file version '%d'\n", version ));
2355 MessageBox( TheEditor->getWindowHandle(),
2356 "Old layout version, cannot open.", "Old File", MB_OK );
2357 return FALSE;
2358
2359 } // end if
2360
2361 // default text colors
2362 fscanf( fp, "Enabled Text: (%d,%d,%d,%d)\n", &colorR, &colorG, &colorB, &colorA );
2363 m_enabledText.color = GameMakeColor( colorR, colorG, colorB, colorA );
2364 fscanf( fp, "Enabled Text Border: (%d,%d,%d,%d)\n", &colorR, &colorG, &colorB, &colorA );
2365 m_enabledText.borderColor = GameMakeColor( colorR, colorG, colorB, colorA );
2366
2367 fscanf( fp, "Disabled Text: (%d,%d,%d,%d)\n", &colorR, &colorG, &colorB, &colorA );
2368 m_disabledText.color = GameMakeColor( colorR, colorG, colorB, colorA );
2369 fscanf( fp, "Disabled Text Border: (%d,%d,%d,%d)\n", &colorR, &colorG, &colorB, &colorA );
2370 m_disabledText.borderColor = GameMakeColor( colorR, colorG, colorB, colorA );
2371
2372 fscanf( fp, "Hilite Text: (%d,%d,%d,%d)\n", &colorR, &colorG, &colorB, &colorA );
2373 m_hiliteText.color = GameMakeColor( colorR, colorG, colorB, colorA );
2374 fscanf( fp, "Hilite Text Border: (%d,%d,%d,%d)\n", &colorR, &colorG, &colorB, &colorA );
2375 m_hiliteText.borderColor = GameMakeColor( colorR, colorG, colorB, colorA );
2376
2377 // default font
2378 char fontBuffer[ 256 ];
2379 Int size, bold;
2380 char c = fgetc( fp );
2381
2382 // skip past the first quote
2383 while( c != '\"' )
2384 c = fgetc( fp );
2385 c = fgetc( fp ); // the quote itself
2386
2387 // copy the name till the next quote is read

2396 fontBuffer[ index ] = '\0';
2397 c = fgetc( fp ); // the end quite itself
2398
2399 // read the size and bold data elements
2400 fscanf( fp, " Size: %d Bold: %d\n", &size, &bold );
2401
2402 // set the font
2403 m_font = TheFontLibrary->getFont( AsciiString(fontBuffer), size, bold );
2404
2405 // all the data for all the states
2406 Int numStates, state;
2407 char imageBuffer[ 128 ];
2408 fscanf( fp, "Number of states: %d\n", &numStates );
2409 for( Int i = 0; i < numStates; i++ )
2410 {
2411
2412 // read all the data
2413 fscanf( fp, "%d: Image: %s Color: (%d,%d,%d,%d) Border: (%d,%d,%d,%d)\n",
2414 &state, imageBuffer, &colorR, &colorG, &colorB, &colorA,
2415 &bColorR, &bColorG, &bColorB, &bColorA );

2425
